channel.title: Problem: Bringing my server online Ip Problems
channel.description:
Ok heres my situation.
I have a vista 64-bit and I have a 525 source folder compiler and runserver works fine
I've downloaded No-IP and regesterd a ip address.
I've got the latest JDK
And I made sure the server was turned on before I try to connect with the client
I port forwarded on my routers page and my computer game port 1 & 2.
127.0.0.1 works but the ip I have regesterd on no-ip doesnt....
Please tell me what I should do?
I feel like it has to do with my ISP Page maybe?
Please reply!

item.title: Problem: Bringing my server online Ip Problems
item.dc:creator: @IceTICKER IceTICKER
item.description:
@IceTICKER wrote:

PortForward.

Depending on your router, all routers should portforward,

Go to Cmd/Ipconfig, Get Your Default IP Address, Type it in your internet browser, & There is your solution.
